# Force LF in the repository and in every checked-out working tree, on every OS.
#
# Why this file exists: LoadBearing pins byte-exact strings in tests — raw-string literals compared
# against `string.Join("\n", …)`, and SHA-256 digests taken over baseline files (GRAMMAR §4). GitHub's
# Windows runners set `core.autocrlf=true`, so without this the checkout rewrites LF→CRLF and those
# pins diverge: a CRLF raw-string literal no longer equals an LF join, and a CRLF baseline no longer
# hashes to its LF digest. Pinning `eol=lf` makes the working tree identical on Windows, Linux, and
# macOS, independent of each machine's git config.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary types must never be line-ending-normalized, should any be added later.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.snk binary
*.nupkg binary
